[size=18pt][b][color=#3b82f6]v7.4.2 RELEASE HIGHLIGHTS[/color][/b][/size]

Today's release fixes critical emission controller bugs and confirms mining works across all production servers:

[b][color=#ef4444]Critical Fixes:[/color][/b]
[list]
[li][b]Emission Genesis Timestamp[/b] - REHEARSAL_GENESIS_TIMESTAMP was off by exactly 1 year (Feb 2025 instead of Feb 2026). Emission target was 2.6M QUG instead of the correct ~12K QUG for elapsed time. [color=#22c55e]FIXED[/color][/li]
[li][b]Persisted State Override[/b] - EmissionController state serialized to RocksDB included a stale genesis timestamp. On restart, the old value overwrote the corrected value. Added set_genesis_timestamp() method to force-correct after restore. [color=#22c55e]FIXED[/color][/li]
[li][b]Height Regression Protection[/b] - Safe floor mechanism (v7.4.1) confirmed working: nodes restart at correct height via persisted safe_floor, not falling back to genesis scan. [color=#22c55e]VERIFIED[/color][/li]
[/list]

[b][color=#f59e0b]Other Fixes:[/color][/b]
[list]
[li][b]Hardcoded Genesis in lib.rs[/b] - Two instances of hardcoded genesis_timestamp=1700000000 (Nov 2023 testnet value) replaced with active_genesis_timestamp()[/li]
[li][b]Pool Topics Wire Format[/b] - Gossipsub pool topics used display_name() (human-readable) instead of as_str() (wire format), breaking P2P pool communication[/li]
[li][b]RocksDB Memory Management[/b] - Block cache capped at 4096MB (was auto-scaling to 16GB, causing OOM)[/li]
[/list]

